### Docker Base Images

Approved base image tags for use in `FROM` (Dockerfiles) and `image:` (compose files). New or updated Dockerfiles and compose files should use only these tags or document an exception.

| Base Image | Approved Tag(s) | Purpose |
|------------|-----------------|---------|
| python | 3.13-slim | Python apps (builder + production stages) |
| node | 18-alpine, 20-alpine | Node/front-end build and dev |
| nginx | 1.27-alpine, 1.29-alpine | Static file serving, reverse proxy |
| postgres | 16-alpine, 17 | Database |
| redis | 7-alpine | Cache |

**Rules:**
- Do not use bare `:latest` or untagged images in Dockerfiles or production compose files.
- Production compose files should use `${VERSION}` for own images (no default `:latest`).
- When upgrading base images, update this table first, then roll out to projects.
- See `rg-common/docs/Docker-standards.md` for full Dockerfile and compose best practices.

